    "summary": "\u2726 Work experience in general\nMore than 40 years of worldwide experience in engineering and commissioning in industrial automation.\nHave good communication skills, am stress-resistant, have problem-solving ability, able to work in a team or independently, have excellent Dutch, German and English language skills.\n\n\u2726 At which companies\nWorked for BBC (Brown, Boveri & Cie), later became ABB (ASEA Brown Boveri), in Mannheim (Germany) from 1981 to 1997. In 1998 started my own company MADE Ingenieursburo in Breda (the Netherlands) and worked mainly for ABB in China and India.\n\n\u2726 In which business sectors\nWorking in the metal industry, steel and aluminium.\nInstallations such as continuous casting, cold and hot-rolling mills, profile mills, processing lines, material handling.\nAlso worked for short periods in power plants and process industry such as cement and dairy.\n\n\u2726 Which activities\nEngineering and commissioning of application software in industrial automation.\nDeveloping of software standards e.g. for seamless tube mills.\nAlso specify and describe process functionality, consult, modify, troubleshoot, test, train.\n\n\u2726 Which systems\nMainly BBC and ABB equipment; hardwired binary and analog control, PLC's.\n\n\u2726Specialties, particular controls:\n\u2022 control/synchronise/balance of position/speed/torque of drives\n\u2022 analyse undesirable control behaviour (instability, oscillations)\n    and counteract by filters, adaptiv control parameters\n\u2022 material tracking on PLC level, to supervise sensors and to communicate with a higher level system\n\u2022 coiler controls, diameter/speed/tension calculation (strip mill)\n\u2022 elongation control (Skin Pass Mill)\n\u2022 Hydraulic Gap Control (HGC)\n\u2022 Automatic Gauge Control (AGC)\n\u2022 flying shear (wire/rod mills)\n\u2022 alignment of rolled material by braking-slides on cooling-bed (rod mills)\n\u2022 length optimisation on cooling bed, as equal lengths (including last) as possible (rod mills)\n\u2022 Laying Head positioning (wire mills)\n\u2022 Tundish Weight Control (continuous casting)\n\u2022 Mould Level Control (continuous casting)",
